---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const candidates = [
  { id: 'typescript', name: 'TypeScript', status: 'Current reference', description: 'The working compiler and complete 41 × 4 evidence catalog.', href: '/typescript/', detail: '164 browser-verified surfaces' },
  { id: 'go', name: 'Go', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Native binary candidate focused on simple distribution, startup time, and concurrency.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
  { id: 'rust', name: 'Rust', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Native candidate focused on throughput, memory use, correctness, and parallel compilation.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
  { id: 'zig', name: 'Zig', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Small native binary candidate with explicit allocation and a minimal runtime surface.', detail: 'Benchmark implementation pending' },
  { id: 'mitosis', name: 'Mitosis', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Builder.io Mitosis generation tested against Kumo APIs, native SSR, hydration, focus, types, and package output.', detail: 'Architectural bake-off pending' },
  { id: 'shared-core', name: 'Shared core', status: 'Coming soon', description: 'Framework-neutral state and behavior with thin native React, Vue, Svelte, and Solid views.', detail: 'Architectural bake-off pending' },
];
---
<Layout title="Kumo compiler candidates">
  <header class="intro">
    <p class="eyebrow">Kumo compiler study</p>
    <h1>Which implementation should compile Kumo?</h1>
    <p>We have one working TypeScript reference compiler. Next we will implement the same normalized contract in Go, Rust, and Zig, run each against the same 41-component fixture set, and compare output correctness, build throughput, startup time, memory, binary size, and maintenance cost before choosing a reference implementation.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="rules" aria-labelledby="rules-title"><h2 id="rules-title">One benchmark contract</h2><p>Every candidate must consume the same <code>kumo.ir/v1</code> input, produce equivalent framework source, pass the same browser and provenance gates, and report raw repeatable measurements. A faster compiler does not win if its output or developer workflow is weaker.</p></section>

  <section class="candidates" aria-labelledby="candidate-title"><div class="heading"><h2 id="candidate-title">Compiler candidates</h2><p>TypeScript is available now. The native implementations are intentionally marked pending until real code and measurements exist.</p></div><div class="grid">
    {candidates.map(candidate => candidate.href ? <a class="card active" href={candidate.href}><span class="status">{candidate.status}</span><h3>{candidate.name}</h3><p>{candidate.description}</p><small>{candidate.detail}</small><b>View compiler results →</b></a> : <article class="card"><span class="status pending">{candidate.status}</span><h3>{candidate.name}</h3><p>{candidate.description}</p><small>{candidate.detail}</small></article>)}
  </div></section>

  <section class="roadmap" aria-labelledby="roadmap-title"><div class="heading"><h2 id="roadmap-title">Roadmap</h2><p>Prove the compiler, compare implementations, then make the result useful.</p></div><ol>
    <li class="done"><div class="rail"><span>✓</span></div><div class="step"><div class="step-head"><small>Phase 1</small><b>Done</b></div><strong>TypeScript reference compiler</strong><p>Working across the current 41 executable targets with normalized IR, native framework outputs, package provenance, and selected browser evidence.</p><a href="/typescript/">View TypeScript results →</a></div></li>
    <li class="active"><div class="rail"><span>2</span></div><div class="step"><div class="step-head"><small>Phase 2</small><b>In progress</b></div><strong>Compare compiler languages</strong><p>Implement the shared planning protocol in Go, Rust, and Zig. Collect comparable raw samples for throughput, startup, memory, and distribution size.</p><div class="languages"><span>Go</span><span>Rust</span><span>Zig</span></div></div></li>
    <li><div class="rail"><span>3</span></div><div class="step"><div class="step-head"><small>Phase 3</small><b>Next</b></div><strong>Run the architectural bake-off</strong><p>Compare the internal compiler, Builder.io Mitosis, and a shared behavior core on seven representative Kumo components using the same browser-backed gates.</p><div class="languages"><span>Internal</span><span>Mitosis</span><span>Shared core</span></div></div></li>
    <li><div class="rail"><span>4</span></div><div class="step"><div class="step-head"><small>Phase 4</small><b>Planned</b></div><strong>Choose, then focus on DX and AX</strong><p>Select from evidence, design Svelte/Vue/Solid consumer workflows, rehearse upstream changes, and prepare the Brandon/Brayden proposal.</p></div></li>
  </ol></section>
</Layout>
<style>
.intro{max-width:850px;padding:34px 0 14px}.eyebrow{margin:0 0 12px;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;font-weight:750;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.intro h1{margin:0;font-size:clamp(38px,5vw,58px);line-height:1.05;letter-spacing:-.045em}.intro>p:last-child{margin:22px 0 0;color:#475569;font-size:18px;line-height:1.65}.rules{max-width:850px;margin-top:42px;padding-top:22px;border-top:1px solid #d8dde5}.rules h2,.roadmap h2,.heading h2{margin:0;font-size:24px;letter-spacing:-.025em}.rules p,.heading p{margin:8px 0 0;color:#64748b;line-height:1.6}.candidates{margin-top:48px}.heading{display:flex;align-items:end;justify-content:space-between;gap:30px;margin-bottom:16px}.heading p{max-width:540px;font-size:13px}.grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));gap:12px}.card{display:block;min-height:210px;padding:20px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:10px;background:#fff;color:inherit;text-decoration:none}.card.active{border-color:#94a3b8}.card.active:hover{border-color:#475569}.status{display:inline-block;color:#166534;font-size:11px;font-weight:750;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:.05em}.status.pending{color:#64748b}.card h3{margin:14px 0 8px;font-size:25px;letter-spacing:-.03em}.card p{margin:0;color:#475569;line-height:1.55}.card small{display:block;margin-top:22px;color:#64748b}.card b{display:block;margin-top:14px;color:#0759b6;font-size:13px}.roadmap{margin-top:52px}.roadmap ol{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,minmax(0,1fr));margin:18px 0 0;padding:0;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:12px;background:#fff;list-style:none}.roadmap li{display:grid;grid-template-columns:34px 1fr;gap:12px;min-width:0;padding:20px 18px;border-left:1px solid #e5e7eb}.roadmap li:first-child{border-left:0}.roadmap li.active{background:#fafbff}.rail{position:relative}.rail::after{content:"";position:absolute;top:32px;bottom:-21px;left:14px;width:1px;background:#e2e8f0}.roadmap li:last-child .rail::after{display:none}.rail>span{display:grid;width:29px;height:29px;place-items:center;border:1px solid #cbd5e1;border-radius:50%;background:#fff;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;font-weight:800}.done .rail>span{border-color:#16a34a;background:#dcfce7;color:#166534}.active .rail>span{border-color:#5264ae;background:#eef0ff;color:#4353a1}.step{min-width:0}.step-head{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;gap:8px;margin-bottom:12px}.step-head small{color:#94a3b8;font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}.step-head b{padding:3px 7px;border-radius:999px;background:#f1f5f9;color:#64748b;font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.06em;text-transform:uppercase}.done .step-head b{background:#dcfce7;color:#166534}.active .step-head b{background:#eef0ff;color:#4353a1}.roadmap li strong{display:block;font-size:15px;line-height:1.3}.roadmap li p{margin:7px 0 0;color:#64748b;font-size:12px;line-height:1.55}.roadmap li a{display:inline-block;margin-top:12px;color:#0759b6;font-size:11px;font-weight:750;text-decoration:none}.languages{display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:5px;margin-top:12px}.languages span{padding:4px 7px;border:1px solid #d8dde5;border-radius:5px;background:#fff;color:#475569;font-size:10px;font-weight:750}@media(max-width:900px){.roadmap ol{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr))}.roadmap li:nth-child(3){border-left:0;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb}.roadmap li:nth-child(4){border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb}}@media(max-width:700px){.heading{display:block}.grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}.intro>p:last-child{font-size:16px}.card{min-height:0}.roadmap ol{grid-template-columns:1fr}.roadmap li,.roadmap li:nth-child(3),.roadmap li:nth-child(4){border-left:0;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb}.roadmap li:first-child{border-top:0}.rail::after{display:block}.roadmap li:last-child .rail::after{display:none}}
</style>
